Like it was shot with a mobile phone because this was in 2010 not in the 90s but still. We never actually put it together and made it an actual film but what is it with British preteens and wanting to make horror films?😂

ACTUALLY I JUST REMEMBERED WE DID IT TWICE. Once when we were like 13 and once more when we were like 14/15 and we actually posted it on Facebook and it still makes me laugh😂

summary: Here's a good question. Why do people treat Dan so much more poorly than they do Phil? Like everytime Dan does something or...
question: Here's a good question. Why do people treat Dan so much more poorly than they do Phil? Like everytime Dan does something or doesn't do something, hes met with backlash. Phil doesn't have the same thing happen, at least not to the same degree.  Any thoughts?
answer:
It is a really good question and I don’t have a good answer. Whenever this topic comes up I always end up with anons in my inbox telling me that Phil does get treated poorly, but objectively I just don’t see him getting the same level of vitriol that I see directed at Dan. People write pages worth of posts just absolutely picking apart Dan’s behavior and personality and it’s really perverse at times. It’s not some special flaw of Dan’s that causes this either because Phil has things that could be picked at too, ever single person on this planet does, but for some reason, when it comes to Dan, the appropriate boundaries people have with others seem to fly out the window. I will say that I do think the majority of the phandom are a lot more invested in Dan than they are in Phil and I think that plays a big part, but I don’t think that’s the only factor.

Does anyone else have any thoughts on this topic? I’d be really interested to hear any theories.
